50|$|As {{carbines}} were reconditioned, parts such as {{the magazine}} catch, rear sight, barrel band without bayonet lug, and stock were upgraded with current standard-issue parts. Also, both during and after WW2, many semi-automatic M1 carbines were converted to select-fire M2 carbines by using the T17 and T18 conversion kits. The conversion included a modified sear and slide and added a disconnector, <b>disconnector</b> <b>lever,</b> and selector switch that could be set for semi-auto or full-automatic fire.|$|E

